{
  "stem": "2533.3",
  "chunk_idx": 16,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I didn't get much because I didn't leave myself that much to have a few more mark.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And from there, I went to Berlin.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "In Berlin, we had to get out of the train because there was an air raid.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We got into the bunkers-- bunkers you say in English.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And then from-- when I came up, I got onto the wrong train.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Instead to go to Halle, I went to Hanover.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I couldn't change it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I had to-- to stop in Hanover.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I got out.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And I saw somebody, a young man with a P on the arm, because all the foreign workers had initials of the country.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I think so, because that was for Poland.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I went over to him and asked him, you know, I have to go to Frankfurt.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I know I'm on the wrong track-- how to get via Halle to Frankfurt.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And a German-- what is it called, like-- like the one who works there, but he was in that navy uniform, from the trains?",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he talked to him in German, where I want to go.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I showed him, I had a red ticket that is [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he said not to worry.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "At 2 o'clock in the morning, there will be a train from Hanover to [NON-ENGLISH], only for Germans.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But if I go in there and don't speak to anybody and try to sit near a window where there are curtains, because it has to be camouflaged for the light, and pretend that you are asleep, and if they will come to ask you for the ticket, all they will do is ask you to get off the next station.",
      "word_count": 61
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That's all.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And if not, you might get through.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
